The paper is about improving the performance of recommender systems using artificial intelligence techniques. It specifically focuses on utilizing Heterogeneous Information Networks (HIN) to address the data sparsity and cold start problems in collaborative filtering-based recommendation methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases).
